caption: The yellow curry with crispy chicken was so good we ordered it AGAIN to go. Plus the service (from Jiapong) was impeccable, easy 5/5.

Favorite Thai place!!!! The food is always so fresh and delicious. Staff are extremely friendly. I would give 10 stars if I could!

Excellent customer service, my boyfriend has a nut allergy and they called especially to doublecheck an appetizer that contained some nuts, and gave us a great recommendation instead. The food was delicious, especially the Massaman curry and crispy chicken are absolutely delicious. Portions are huge for a decent price. Loved it!
This is a surefire Thai option. Their curries and pad thai are delicious.

Ordered for pickup on a Friday night and they were very quick! We got the pineapple fried rice, khao soi, and papaya salad. The fried rice was pretty standard. I really liked the khao soi though. I got mild spicy I think and it was pretty spicy for my tastebuds already, but I think for someone who likes spice it would be pretty good. They also give you a lot of curry so I ended up using the leftover with rice the next day! The papaya salad was pretty good too. I think it was even spicier than the khao soi, but refreshing! Would definitely be interested in ordering from here again!

Great food! Delicious and crispy spring rolls. Best takeout experience during COVID yet — was still warm by the time I got home. I’ve been avoiding takeout for the most part during the pandemic because the food is always soggy and the experience is diminished, but keeping this place in my back pocket as an option in the future!
Best Thai food in Williamsburg!  We love the green curry, pad thai, and pad sew ew.  Highly recommend!
Hole in the wall. Take out spot. With 2 tables

This casual Thai place is a staple. Drunken noodles and pad see ew might be on the greasy side but still very tasty when it's tossed in good wok hei--very hot wok. The brothy duck noodle soup is very flavorful and comforting, especially for cold weather. Fried chive cakes are soft and chewy, to be dipped in a light salty, tangy sauce--a must order for me.

I recently moved to this area and wanted to find a nice authentic thai spot. this place has nailed it. after spending 6 weeks in thailand I really value when thai restaurants remind me of my time there (i know i am no expert tho). everything tastes fresh and delicious. i won't be ordering thai from anywhere else

Tiny spot on Metropolitan Ave, got the shrimp Tom yum soup and basil fried rice with beef. Friendly service but the food wasn’t very complex in flavor like I’ve come to expect from Thai. Will try and again and edit if I like it the next time.
Best Thai food in Williamsburg. Fantastic food and the best service!!
Cute delicious neighborhood Thai. Great service and the sweetest, kindest staff!
Food was so amazing!!! The calamari is fried tubes instead of rings (still delicious)!
Food is great and in big quantities!
Great food. Great service!

Very friendly, fast service. I called and ordered in advance for a later pickup. When I arrived to pick up they were finalizing the order - Which I appreciated as this meant the order was not sitting around. I ordered the fried tofu appetizer with peanut sauce, Pad See Ew noodles with chicken and Kra-Pow with shrimp.  The fried tofu and pad see ew noodles were both very bland in flavor. I would not recommend either. The Kra-Pow was decent but not memorable. It was not very spicy and while significantly better than the other two dishes, did not compare favorably to the same dish I have had at other Thai restaurants.  Given the exceptional overall rating on Google (4.9 stars) I expected much better.

I ordered from here for our company lunch day. With a huge order delivered in under an hour we were initially impressed and were equally delighted when we bit into our food. I highly recommended the pulled jackfruit rice it's a light delightful treat. When we realized they forgot a drink -it was a huge order- they were so kind to take care of it right away and even gave us an extra dessert!! A simply wonderful experience
Great food, server Anna is amazing
Very great Thai restaurant.. I had a fried rice with shrimp 🍤 I love it I love their food amazing And Kook she was great she had a great customer service experience love it love their service
Savory thai is amazing!! I love their dishes. :)
The food here is amazing, everything on the menu is great! The vibe is so cute and comfy, and the service is amazing. Everyone who works at Savory is so sweet and helpful.

Actually sooo good. Love this place. We ordered pad thai with duck and oh my god. For a such a small restaurant, the duck is like grade A; so tender. The tea is also so good. If you dont like super sweet boba/thai tea then this is your restaurant to order boba and some food to go with it. The staff are so nice, especially Anna.

We found this amazing hole in a wall in Brooklyn. Best tea ever and best pad thai in the planet! A must visit place, save the plane ride to Thailand and head straight to Brooklyn and look for Anna banana. Always ask for a recommendation and she will gladly help. Kob khun
This is definitely a must come and taste! Try the pad Thai w duck! The duck was absolutely crunchy tender and juicy. Anna was a great host: friendly warm and such a joy.
This is the best Thai food in the Williamsburg area. Delicious, affordable and generous portions. Well worth the 15 min walk over. Will be back soon!
Staff are very kind and friendly!! Variety of food and drink. Food was delicious and fast. Recommend spot for have a quick meal.

What a great local spot! For starters, we had the Thai wings and the shrimp dumplings (fried) which were so flavorful and unique. Then for the main dishes we tried the Singapore noodles with shrimp (have them make it spicy, it is amazing!), and the crispy chicken over fried rice which did not disappoint. Not only was the food some of the best Thai I've had in a long time, but the customer service was superb. Highly recommend.
Cute,quaint  place with amazing food and service!
Great Thai food, and you can get a $1 Thai ice tea with the lunch special.
